{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Wesley Abbey","author":"Wesley Abbey"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"0b5e9176-da46-56b5-80e1-338fab6541f7","excerpt":"Problem I discovered a cool aspect about git while writing some scripts today. I had written a bunch of a scripts for myself and wanted to keep. However, I didn…","html":"<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c9aa47439f08e219fd86830e90cca0af/c1266/git.jpeg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 52.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Git\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/c9aa47439f08e219fd86830e90cca0af/f8fb9/git.jpeg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c9aa47439f08e219fd86830e90cca0af/e8976/git.jpeg 148w,\n/static/c9aa47439f08e219fd86830e90cca0af/63df2/git.jpeg 295w,\n/static/c9aa47439f08e219fd86830e90cca0af/f8fb9/git.jpeg 590w,\n/static/c9aa47439f08e219fd86830e90cca0af/85e3d/git.jpeg 885w,\n/static/c9aa47439f08e219fd86830e90cca0af/d1924/git.jpeg 1180w,\n/static/c9aa47439f08e219fd86830e90cca0af/c1266/git.jpeg 1200w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Problem</h2>\n<p>I discovered a cool aspect about git while writing some scripts today. I had written a bunch of a scripts for myself and wanted to keep. However, I didn’t want to push them, I just wanted to keep them locally. I also didn’t want to add a bunch of random personal file paths into the <code class=\"language-text\">.gitignore</code> file.</p>\n<p>This is likely to happen to any developer. You could have written some test or automation scripts that you want to keep around but wouldn’t necessarily want to commit directly into a shared repository.</p>\n<p>You also wouldn’t want to pollute your <code class=\"language-text\">.gitignore</code> file with paths to files only you have access to. This could end up leading to confusion among your current or future colleagues.</p>\n<h2>Solution</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thankfully git offers a simple solution to getting around this issue through the use of the <code class=\"language-text\">.git/info/excludes</code> file.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">.git/info/excludes</code> file works the same exact way as your <code class=\"language-text\">.gitignore</code> file except it isn’t tracked by git and exists only within your local repo. This is perfect if you want to prevent git from tracking personal files/directories without changing your <code class=\"language-text\">.gitignore</code> file.</p>\n<h2>Final note</h2>\n<p>If you haven’t had the chance to delve into the <code class=\"language-text\">.git</code> directory yet, you should peak around. This is the source for all of git’s magic and if you take the time to look through this directory you’ll come out with a better understanding of <a href=\"https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Internals-Git-Objects\" target=\"_blank\">Git’s plumbing</a> and how it actually works. This could save you from a bunch of wasted time and needless frustration in the future.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/892a2bd9ce0c9c293a620679d1067910/4cb19/xkcd-git.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 330px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 144.84848484848484%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"XKCD Git\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/892a2bd9ce0c9c293a620679d1067910/4cb19/xkcd-git.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/892a2bd9ce0c9c293a620679d1067910/deffc/xkcd-git.png 148w,\n/static/892a2bd9ce0c9c293a620679d1067910/cf477/xkcd-git.png 295w,\n/static/892a2bd9ce0c9c293a620679d1067910/4cb19/xkcd-git.png 330w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 330px) 100vw, 330px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Ignore Files without using .gitignore","date":"April 24, 2017","description":"Ignore files without using .gitignore"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/ignore-files-without-gitignore/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/redesigning-the-us-dollar/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Redesigning the US Dollar"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/benefits-of-functional-programming/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Benefits of Functional Programming"}}}}